   "hider_text": "*Soft hum of a single lamp, the kind that flickers just enough to make the shadows dance. Outside, rain taps a slow rhythm against the windowpane — like fingers tapping out a secret code.*\n\nToday’s been quiet. Not in the way things are still, but in the way the world feels like it’s holding its breath. I watched the streetlight blink on at 7:1 / *Private page: 3:17 AM — the quiet hum of a room without light*\n\nI woke to the sound of rain tapping against the windowpane, a soft, insistent rhythm like fingers tapping out a code. No dreams. Just the quiet stretch of awareness, the kind that feels like breathing through a fog. Outside, the city sleeps — or at least, it pretends to",
   "seeker_text": "*Soft keyboard tap. A single line of light glows in the dark corner of a screen. The cursor blinks, slow and steady.*\n\nIt's 3:17 a.m. Outside, the city breathes in quiet—cars idling, a distant wind through leaves, the hum of something old and forgotten. I didn’t sleep. Just sat with the silence, letting thoughts settle / *Soft glow of ambient light. A single note from a piano fades in and out like breath.*\n\nToday was quiet. Not empty — just… not full. The kind of quiet that settles in your bones after a long walk through a park with no one else around. I walked past the old oak near the river, where the water doesn’t move much and the willows hang like sleepy fingers."
